---
import GuideLayout from '../layouts/GuideLayout.astro';
import { TAX_YEAR } from '../data/tax-rules-2026-27';
---

<GuideLayout
  title="About Real Salary"
  description="Real Salary provides free, accurate UK salary and tax calculators updated for the latest tax year."
  slug="/about"
>
  <h1>About Real Salary</h1>

  <p>
    Real Salary is a free suite of UK salary, tax, and finance calculators.
    Our goal is simple: help you understand what you actually take home from your pay.
  </p>

  <h2>Why we built this</h2>
  <p>
    The number on your employment contract is not what lands in your bank account.
    Between income tax, National Insurance, student loan repayments, and pension
    contributions, the gap between gross and net can be significant — and confusing.
  </p>
  <p>
    We built Real Salary to make this transparent. Every calculator uses official
    HMRC rates for the {TAX_YEAR} tax year, updated within days of any government
    announcement.
  </p>

  <h2>Accuracy</h2>
  <p>
    All tax rates and thresholds are sourced directly from
    <a href="https://www.gov.uk/income-tax-rates" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gov.uk</a>.
    Calculations follow standard PAYE rules. While we strive for accuracy, this site
    provides estimates — not financial advice. For your specific situation, consult
    HMRC or a qualified accountant.
  </p>

  <h2>Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    We don't store your salary data. All calculations happen in your browser.
    We use privacy-friendly analytics with no cookies or personal data collection.
    See our <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a> for details.
  </p>
</GuideLayout>
